# PubPlus mobile — example env (placeholders only). Copy to .env and fill in real values.
# Env strategy: consumer_app/docs/environment-strategy.md
# Auth/SSO setup: consumer_app/docs/auth-sso-runbook.md
#
# Local development: use Supabase Dev project URL + anon key (never service role).
# TestFlight / App Store: use Supabase Prod — typically via EAS secrets later, not this file.
#
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8000
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
EXPO_PUBLIC_AUTH_REDIRECT_SCHEME=pubplus

# Frontend-safe EXPO_PUBLIC_* only. Never commit populated .env files.
# Never put Supabase service role keys, DB passwords, or provider client secrets here.
# Provider secrets belong in Supabase Auth and Google/Facebook/Apple dashboards (Stage 5).
#
# OAuth redirect URLs — add per Supabase project (Auth > URL configuration):
#   Dev:  http://localhost:8081/auth/callback
#         http://localhost:8082/auth/callback   (if using alternate Expo web port)
#         pubplus://auth/callback
#   Prod: same pubplus:// pattern + production web origins when known
#         https://<project-ref>.supabase.co/auth/v1/callback  (provider dashboards)
#
# Web OAuth: browser origin + /auth/callback (see getOAuthRedirectUrl in lib/supabase.ts).
# Native OAuth: EXPO_PUBLIC_AUTH_REDIRECT_SCHEME + auth/callback (default pubplus).
#
# Legacy / Replit — omit unless Replit deploy is confirmed active:
# EXPO_PUBLIC_DOMAIN=your-replit-domain.replit.dev
